5.1.1 Video Content Translation
Users must be able to watch video content in any supported language. Closed captions, Audio Descriptions, and Secondary Audio Programming must be clearly labeled and quickly accessible.

5.1.1-A
Closed captioning must be provided in all supported languages.

5.1.1-B
Audio descriptions must be provided in all supported languages. 

5.1.1-C
Supported languages must have Secondary Audio Programming to allow users to watch content in their native languages. English and Spanish content is required to be present, but additional language support is encouraged.
